# Source: vos_codons_64x4facets.json (256 Facet Interpretive Library)

**Provenance:** `codex/vrc_static_signature/vos_codons_64x4facets.json` (215 KB, 3334 lines including markdown wrapper)  
**Nature:** Structured interpretive data for the complete 256-state system

## What This File Contains

This is the **authoritative dataset for all 64 codons × 4 facets = 256 interpretive states**.

Each codon entry includes:

- Core identity: `id`, `code` (RC01–RC64), `name`, `traditional_name`, `binary` (6-bit), `chemical_marker`, `archetype_role`, `somatic_marker`
- Frequency spectrum: Shadow / Gift / Siddhi with rich descriptions
- Full facet breakdown for A (Somatic), B (Relational), C (Cognitive), D (Transpersonal):
  - Precise degree range within the codon (e.g., 0° – 1.40625°)
  - Description of the lived experience
  - `shadow_manifestation`
  - Specific `micro_correction` (actionable, somatic/relational/cognitive/transpersonal)
  - `resonance_keys` (tagging for search / connection)

## Significance

In the VRC Static Signature Product Research Report (ingested alongside this file), one of the largest acknowledged implementation gaps was:

> “the complete 256 facet interpretation library”

This JSON appears to be the (or a major) realization of that missing library. It provides the detailed, living language for every possible codon + facet combination that the engine can activate.

## Structure Highlights

- 64 top-level codon objects in array form
- Every facet carries its own micro-correction — this is extremely valuable for ORIEL narration and report generation
- Rich somatic, relational, cognitive, and transpersonal differentiation per codon
- Binary signatures and chemical markers suggest deeper biological / resonant mapping layers

## Usage in the System

This data is the interpretive heart that turns raw codon + facet activations (from the Mandala mapping + Prime Stack engines) into human-meaningful, actionable language.

It sits one layer above the pure mathematical canon (the Unified Specification + VRC Engine Canon) and one layer below the final ORIEL transmission or visual report.

